acoustically challenging

00:05:47.820 --> 00:05:49.770
situations--

00:05:49.770 --> 00:05:54.230
listening to your dinner
date in a loud restaurant,

00:05:54.230 --> 00:05:59.670
trying to listen to a caller
in a loud airport lounge,

00:05:59.670 --> 00:06:04.320
listening to our presenter
who is speaking too softly,

00:06:04.320 --> 00:06:06.930
like me right now.

00:06:06.930 --> 00:06:09.750
One could think about
environmental noise

00:06:09.750 --> 00:06:12.840
as a form of
situational disability,

00:06:12.840 --> 00:06:15.810
but what if you could
turn down the noise

00:06:15.810 --> 00:06:18.700
and boost the signal
on your smartphone

00:06:18.700 --> 00:06:23.640
so you would never
miss the conversation?

00:06:23.640 --> 00:06:29.610
Now you can, because today we're
introducing Sound Amplifier.

00:06:29.610 --> 00:06:32.760
Sound Amplifier is a new
accessibility service

00:06:32.760 --> 00:06:37.170
that helps users focus on
real world conversations using

00:06:37.170 --> 00:06:42.690
only an Android smartphone
and a set of headphones.

00:06:42.690 --> 00:06:46.110
Users can tune hundreds
of personalized levels

00:06:46.110 --> 00:06:48.330
to optimize their
listening experience

00:06:48.330 --> 00:06:50.820
to the current environment.

00:06:50.820 --> 00:06:54.000
Its two sliders, for
loudness and tuning,

00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:57.930
dynamically adjust
over 100 audio presets

00:06:57.930 --> 00:06:59.520
in the background.

00:06:59.520 --> 00:07:02.370
The settings can then
be independently applied

00:07:02.370 --> 00:07:04.110
to each ear.

00:07:04.110 --> 00:07:07.800
Adjusting them provides
ambient sound--

00:07:07.800 --> 00:07:12.790
improves ambient sound quality
in a vast array of scenarios,

00:07:12.790 --> 00:07:17.430
including enhancing sound in
loud, distant, or far away

00:07:17.430 --> 00:07:23.640
spaces, increasing the volume
of somebody who speaks softly,

00:07:23.640 --> 00:07:26.340
turning up the TV
to a volume that's

00:07:26.340 --> 00:07:30.420
understandable and acceptable
for everybody in the room.

00:07:30.420 --> 00:07:32.910
Now, I'm going to
briefly explain

00:07:32.910 --> 00:07:36.390
how it was built using the new
dynamics processing effect.

00:07:39.720 --> 00:07:44.430
Sound Amplifier was built on the
new dynamics processing effect

00:07:44.430 --> 00:07:47.190
in Android's audio framework.

00:07:47.190 --> 00:07:50.280
The effect is based on a
four-stage signal processing

00:07:50.280 --> 00:07:52.140
architecture.

00:07:52.140 --> 00:07:54.630
Stage one is pre-equalization.

00:07:54.630 --> 00:07:57.240
You could think about
the pre-equalizer

00:07:57.240 --> 00:08:02.880
as a programmatic way to
adjust any audio frequency.

00:08:02.880 --> 00:08:07.020
Think bass to treble and
everything in between.

00:08:07.020 --> 00:08:11.010
Stage two is a
multi-band compressor.

00:08:11.010 --> 00:08:13.860
The multi-band compressor
is the keystone

00:08:13.860 --> 00:08:16.620
of the dynamic
processing effect.

00:08:16.620 --> 00:08:20.640
It adjusts soft sounds
and adjusts down loud

00:08:20.640 --> 00:08:24.660
sounds to provide a much
better listening experience.

00:08:24.660 --> 00:08:27.270
Stage three is
post-equalization.

00:08:27.270 --> 00:08:30.300
Similar to the first stage,
it allows you to fine tune

00:08:30.300 --> 00:08:32.650
any audio frequency.

00:08:32.650 --> 00:08:38.370
Lastly, stage four, the limiter,
prevents additional gain

00:08:38.370 --> 00:08:42.539
above a developer designated
threshold, which prevents

00:08:42.539 --> 00:08:45.450
loud or unwanted noises.

00:08:45.450 --> 00:08:48.600
We're going to be doing a
number of demos and a deep dive

00:08:48.600 --> 00:08:52.290
on the dynamics processing
effect and Sound Amplifier

00:08:52.290 --> 00:08:56.200
